metadata.name: DC Franchise Rankings Database
metadata.description: Complete player rankings after Season 5: Rescue Island with weighted scoring system
metadata.source: After Season 5: Rescue Island - Complete Edition

scoringSystem.placement: 40% - Average finish position across all seasons
scoringSystem.socialGame: 15% - Votes received (lower = better), jury votes earned
scoringSystem.strategicImpact: 10% - Idol plays, blindsides executed, game control

A.name: TIER A ‚Äî Elite Threats
A.description: Top 15% ‚Ä¢ Deep runs and strategic excellence

D.name: TIER D ‚Äî Below Average
D.description: Bottom 40% ‚Ä¢ Early boots and limited impact

rankings.title: The Three-Time Finalist
rankings.reasoning: THREE finals appearances (unprecedented in franchise). Season 4 WINNER (7-6-1 closest finale ever). Most challenge wins in franchise history (13 total across 3 seasons). Fire-making champion (defeated Gwen at F4). Runner-up twice (S1: 4-5, S2: 1-5-1) before finally winning. Strategic ranking #1 overall franchise.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S3 or S5

rankings.title: The Perfect Game
rankings.reasoning: Season 5 WINNER with PERFECT GAME (zero votes all season). Won tiebreak 4-3-2 with Ryan casting deciding vote. Elite threat management - never targeted despite strong position. Lulu duo with Dave into merge axis with Ryan. Found auction idol (held for confidence). Quietest threat award winner.

rankings.title: The Social Queen
rankings.reasoning: Season 1 WINNER (5-4 over Alejandro). Most consistent player in franchise - Final Tribal BOTH seasons (1st S1, 3rd S2). Only 2 votes against across entire career (1 S1, 1 S2). Perfect social mastery with zero threat perception.

rankings.title: The Challenge Dominant
rankings.reasoning: Season 5 FINALIST (2nd place). MOST DOMINANT COMPETITOR S5 with 4 challenge wins (3 immunity, 1 reward). Controlled endgame (F6-F4 immunities). TWO PERFECT IDOL PLAYS: F6 saved Sugar forcing Dave boot, F5 saved herself. Lost tiebreak 3-3 to Mickey.

rankings.title: The Loyalist
rankings.reasoning: Season 4 FINALIST (2nd place, lost 6-7 by ONE vote). UNPRECEDENTED 3 unbreakable bonds simultaneously (S4). Only 4 votes against across career. 8 total challenge wins. Closest runner-up in franchise history.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, or S5

rankings.title: The Best to Never Win
rankings.reasoning: TWO finals appearances (2nd S3, 3rd S4) - never won. PERFECT IDOL PLAY S4: held for 9 tribals (franchise record), played at F5 cancelling 3 votes. Most patient idol holder in history. 6 challenge wins all in S3. Strategic rank #2 in franchise.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, or S5

rankings.title: The Underdog Winner
rankings.reasoning: Season 2 WINNER (dominant 5-1-1 victory). Survived constant targeting and earned jury respect despite adversity. Previous winners curse S4 (eliminated Episode 12). Improvement arc: 14th S1 ‚Üí WON S2 ‚Üí 7th S4.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S3 or S5

rankings.title: The Mastermind
rankings.reasoning: BEST STRATEGIC PLAYER Season 5. Reached F4, eliminated at fire-making. 2 immunity wins. Strategic ranking #1 in S5. Major meltdown at F4 hurt fire-making performance.

rankings.title: The Kingmaker
rankings.reasoning: Season 5 3rd place. FAN FAVORITE winner. Won fire-making. CAST DECIDING TIEBREAK VOTE (chose Mickey over Sky). Unbreakable bond with Mickey proved in final vote.

rankings.title: The Evolution
rankings.reasoning: FRANCHISE RECORD: 4 consecutive immunity wins (S4 Episodes 11-14). Massive improvement arc: 16th S1 ‚Üí 8th S2 ‚Üí 4th S4. Fire-making loss to Alejandro at F4. 5 total challenge wins.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S3 or S5

rankings.title: The Cold Calculator
rankings.reasoning: TWO deep runs (3rd S3, 5th S4). Cast deciding tiebreaker vote for Emma S3 (4-3-1). BRUTAL MOVE: Voted out unbreakable Anne Maria S3. Perfect idol play S3. Strategic ranking #3 franchise.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, or S5

rankings.title: The Perfectionist (Cursed)
rankings.reasoning: Season 3 WINNER (4-3-1 tiebreaker). PERFECT GAME S3 (0 votes until F4). Strategic rank #2 in S3. WINNERS CURSE: 1st S3 ‚Üí 17th S4. Eliminated Episode 2 S4 (5-3) as immediate champion threat.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, or S5

rankings.title: The Physical Force
rankings.reasoning: Physical force Season 1 with 5 challenge wins (4 immunity, 1 reward). F3 finish S1. Tiebreaker juror. Strong early-merge player but declined to 14th S2. Elite athletic ability.

rankings.title: The Improver
rankings.reasoning: MASSIVE improvement S1 ‚Üí S2 (5th S1, 4th S2). Perfect idol play S2. 26 votes against total (22 in S1 alone - 2nd most ever). Most loyal player S2. Cast only Lindsay jury vote.

rankings.title: The Villain
rankings.reasoning: THREE seasons (8th S1, 9th S2, 15th S4). Dangerous strategist S1-S2. Found 2 idols S1. Strategic ranking #2 franchise. S4 decline (15th, couldn't adapt). Elite strategic mind but high threat level.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S3 or S5

rankings.title: The Balanced Player
rankings.reasoning: Consistent mid-merge threat (6th S1, 7th S2). 4 total challenge wins. Balanced gameplay. Unbreakable bond partner. Alejandro's target S2 (meltdown victim). Solid but never broke through.

rankings.title: The Chaos Agent
rankings.reasoning: MOST CHAOTIC PLAYER Season 5. 8th place. Weaponized chaos - survived repeatedly from bottom. Reba Beware converted to idol. Inheritance advantage (claim advantages if survives). Eliminated 3-2-1 at F8. Strategic rank #2 S5.

rankings.title: The Improver
rankings.reasoning: MASSIVE improvement: 17th S1 ‚Üí 8th S4 (9 places jump). 3 challenge wins S4. Extra vote advantage S4 Episode 3. Solid strategic and physical game S4.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S2, S3, or S5

rankings.title: The Analyst
rankings.reasoning: Improvement 15th S1 ‚Üí 9th S4. Triple idol tribal S4. Found Yellow Tribe idol S4. Unbreakable bond with Alejandro S4. Strong strategic mind but limited execution.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S2, S3, or S5

rankings.title: The Party Guy (Evolved)
rankings.reasoning: HUGE improvement: 20th S1 ‚Üí 6th S4 (14 places!). FRANCHISE RECORD 42 total votes against. Edge of Extinction return winner Episode 13 (re-eliminated same episode). Ultimate resilience.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S2, S3, or S5

rankings.title: The Multi-Faceted
rankings.reasoning: Multiple unbreakable bonds specialist (6th S3, 12th S4). Victim of Sierra's perfect idol play S4. Strong social player with solid gameplay.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, or S5

rankings.title: The Idol King
rankings.reasoning: MOST IDOLS FOUND IN FRANCHISE: 3 (franchise record). Most idol-aware player. LEGENDARY PLAY: saved Alejandro with idol S2. Deep runs (4th S1, 6th S2). Feud specialist.

rankings.title: The Gentle Giant
rankings.reasoning: HUGE leap: 22nd S1 ‚Üí 5th S2 (17 places!). Kind personality despite physical presence. Made jury S2. Feud with Ezekiel.

rankings.title: The Fighter
rankings.reasoning: THREE seasons (9th S1, 11th S2, 14th S4). Perfect idol play S2. Strategic mind with volatile social game. 32 votes against total. High threat level but resilient.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S3 or S5

rankings.title: The Heart
rankings.reasoning: Strong social bonds (7th S1 medevac, 12th S2). Victim of Courtney's perfect idol play S2. Loveable personality. Fan favorite but early exits.

rankings.title: The Comeback
rankings.reasoning: MASSIVE improvement: First boot S1 (24th) ‚Üí First juror S2 (10th). Fan Favorite S1 despite first boot. Found idol S1 but didn't play it.

rankings.title: The Survivor (S3)
rankings.reasoning: Season 3: 5th place, MOST VOTES AGAINST (15). Unbreakable bond with Cameron (who betrayed her). Survived to F5 despite constant targeting. Note: S3 version only (S4 version separate in Tier D).
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, S4, or S5

rankings.title: The Tragic Hero
rankings.reasoning: MOST TRAGIC EXIT Season 5. 6th place. Had win equity but eliminated at F6 only because Sky's idol saved Sugar. Lulu duo with Mickey. Season-long extreme hatred with Sugar.

rankings.title: The Super Fan
rankings.reasoning: PERFECT IDOL PLAY S4 Episode 7 (10 votes cancelled - franchise record!). Found 2 idols. Strong strategic awareness. 10th S1, 11th S4. 39 total votes against.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S2, S3, or S5

rankings.title: The Competitor
rankings.reasoning: FAN FAVORITE Season 4. 7th S3, 10th S4. FRANCHISE RECORD: 4 extreme hatreds S3. Competitive spirit. 17 total votes against.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, or S5

rankings.title: The Target
rankings.reasoning: MOST VOTES AGAINST Season 5 (10 votes). Reached F5 despite constant targeting. Saved by Sky's idol at F6. Season-long feud with Dave. Eliminated 3-1-1 at F5.

rankings.title: The Evil Twin
rankings.reasoning: Season 5: 7th place, first juror. Eliminated 2-2-1 at F7. Made jury. 3 votes against.

rankings.title: The Cadet
rankings.reasoning: Season 3: 9th place. 1 immunity win. Unbreakable bonds with Dwayne/Mike. Solid mid-merge player. Honor code gameplay.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, S4, or S5

rankings.title: The Straight Shooter
rankings.reasoning: Consistent mid-game elimination (11th S1, 13th S2). Never reached jury. Strong personality. Honest player.

rankings.title: The Survivalist
rankings.reasoning: Season 5: 9th place. Found Belo Beware idol (used on Topher). Amulet trio holder. Eliminated 5-2 at F9. Solid mid-game player.

rankings.title: The Dad
rankings.reasoning: Season 3: 10th place, first juror. Strong social game. Blindsided at merge. Family gameplay.
rankings.status: Did not compete in S1, S2, S4, or S5

rankings.title: The Evil Genius

rankings.title: The BFF
rankings.reasoning: Season 1: 12th place. Found idol Episode 2. MAPLV duo with Sadie. First merge boot.

rankings.title: The Host Wannabe
